 \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's quite something,\\\" Hales said of his new status as an Olympic champion.\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier, in the mixed-team pistol event, Arunovic and Mikec drew level when Turkey's Sevval Ilayda Tarhan and Yusuf Dikec looked on the brink of victory at 14-12 in the race to the magic number of 16.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.983410530417907, \"rank\": 0.016670468070703416, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"score\": 0.9986818055541746, \"rank\": 0.0006901349184811801, \"text\": \"Yusuf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Manu Bhaker and Sarabjot Singh claimed the bronze for India, beating the South Korean pair Oh Ye-jin and Lee Won-ho 16-10.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Manu Bhaker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manu_Bhaker\"}, {\"begin\": 1007, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999850553579426, \"rank\": 1.4510333883641026e-05, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1058, \"end\": 1061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999997253326, \"rank\": 2.7463117770275245e-10, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bhaker, who won bronze in the women's individual event, becomes India's first multi-medallist at an Olympic Games since the country's independence in 1947.\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999850553579426, \"rank\": 1.4510333883641026e-05, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rafa Nadal and Carlos Alcaraz combined their formidable firepower to down Dutchmen Tallon Griekspoor and Wesley Koolhof and reach the quarterfinals of the men's tennis doubles.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1234, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafa Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 1249, \"end\": 1263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallon_Griekspoor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tallon Griekspoor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallon_Griekspoor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallon_Griekspoor\"}, {\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wesley_Koolhof\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wesley Koolhof\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wesley_Koolhof\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wesley_Koolhof\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, women's second seed Coco Gauff's challenge wilted as she was knocked out in the third round 7-6(7) 6-2.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1443, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Coco Gauff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gauff was left in tears at a crucial moment of the second set when an over-ruled line call saw her slip 4-2 behind, with the American becoming embroiled in a lengthy argument with the umpire and tournament supervisor.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9959210468964916, \"rank\": 0.004085600319154977, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"North Korea said they could learn from China after winning their first Olympic medal in eight years, settling for silver after a mixed doubles defeat to the table tennis superpower.\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1786, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998488637392082, \"rank\": 0.00012758065935843829, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China arrived in Paris as the world's undisputed table tennis kings, having won 32 of the 37 available golds since it became an Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998488637392082, \"rank\": 0.00012758065935843829, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1947, \"end\": 1952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999858232514, \"rank\": 1.417661271324159e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They failed to claim the mixed doubles title when it was introduced three years ago in Tokyo but Wang Chuqin and Sun Yingsha set the record straight with an 11-6, 7-11, 11-8, 11-5, 7-11, 11-8 win over North Korea's Ri Jong Sik and Kim Kum Yong.\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2161, \"end\": 2166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9998525913006202, \"rank\": 0.00014742996903332749, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2171, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chuqin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Chuqin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chuqin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chuqin\"}, {\"begin\": 2187, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun_Yingsha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sun Yingsha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun_Yingsha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun_Yingsha\"}, {\"begin\": 2297, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sik_District\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.72248601624927e-16, \"text\": \"Sik\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sik_District\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sik_District\"}, {\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.9995183519695024, \"rank\": 0.0001867230664858693, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For North Korea, they skipped the pandemic-postponed Tokyo Olympics in 2021 over COVID-19 concerns.\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2373, \"end\": 2387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.359544211430365e-14, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9924637561137577, \"rank\": 0.004395269317399674, \